  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesize that older persons (â‰¥45 years) treated with ACEI for HTN
      control will have: i) improved status of bone turnover (decreased P1NP and CTX), and ii)
      decreased levels of RANKL and RANKL/OPG, compared to those not treated with ACEI and not
      using RAS-related medications
    </textblock>
